        <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-red-brand mb-2">Compliance · April 2026 · 10 min read</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4 leading-tight">Fire Extinguisher Inspection in San Jose, CA: What Every Business Owner Needs to Know</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">If you own or manage a commercial property in San Jose, CA, your fire extinguishers are a legal requirement with specific inspection schedules enforced by the San Jose Fire Department. Here's exactly what NFPA 10 and the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR) require, what inspections cost, and how to avoid violations.</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3">San Jose Fire Extinguisher Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The City of San Jose enforces the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR), requiring all commercial properties to maintain portable fire extinguishers in compliance with <a href="/compliance/nfpa-10/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 10</a>. San Jose is Silicon Valley's largest city and home to major corporate campuses for Cisco, Adobe, Samsung, and PayPal along the North First Street corridor. The Japantown, Little Saigon, and Santana Row restaurant districts create concentrated kitchen suppression compliance demand. Data centers and technology research facilities require specialized Class C extinguisher coverage beyond standard commercial ABC units.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Monthly Visual Inspections</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Monthly visual inspections can be performed by trained building staff. Verify each unit is in place, unobstructed, pressure gauge reads in the operating range, tamper seal is intact, and pull pin is present. Document every check — absence of monthly records significantly increases liability exposure.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Annual Professional Inspections</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Annual inspections must be performed by a licensed technician. California requires fire extinguisher service contractors to hold an OSFM license. Verify at osfm.fire.ca.gov before scheduling service. The Santa Clara County Fire Department serves unincorporated county areas — the San Jose Fire Department is the AHJ for buildings within city limits. The technician inspects all components and attaches a dated service tag. Failed units must be immediately serviced, recharged, or replaced.</p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">6-Year Internal Examination & 12-Year Hydrostatic Testing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every six years, stored-pressure units must be internally examined for corrosion and agent degradation. At 12 years, cylinders must pass hydrostatic pressure testing — units that fail are condemned. Your service provider should track these intervals based on each unit's manufacture date.</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Inspection Costs in San Jose, CA</h2>
